  "text": "Simplifications and other discrepancies with the standard We do not consider the distinction between global memory (shared among all threads) and local memory (shared among threads in a work-group), and instead treat all memory as global; local memory is not interesting in the context of memory scopes, since the only allowable scope with which local memory can be accessed atomically is WG. Fences, barriers, relaxed atomics, and sequentially-consistent atomics were not discussed in previous work on RSP [CITATION_1] and are largely orthogonal. OpenCL employs a stricter form of scope inclusion, in which both events must additionally use the same memory scope. The version we use here follows a proposal called HRF-relaxed [CITATION_2] , and is a necessary prerequisite for RSP.",
